news.title: Cidco to hire consultant for generating alternate revenue from Navi Mumbai metro
news.para: Cidco has floated a tender inviting online proposals from internationally experienced and reputed single business entities for appointment as a consultant for assessment of Non-Fare Box Revenue (NFBR) opportunities in Line-1 (Belapur-Pendhar) of Navi Mumbai Metro project.

news.title: Set up university for construction and realty sector courses at NAC: Panel
news.para: The committee, in its report, has recommended that NAC has the funds, land and capacity to set up the university on its campus in the IT corridor. Of the total 40-acre campus, a university can be set up, preferably a private university, in a 20-acre area.

news.title: Welcome decision to give enhanced powers to LPA: CREDAI Coimbatore
news.para: ​CREDAI Coimbatore President Gugan Ilango said the real estate body has been requesting the government to increase the approval powers of the Local Planning Authority.

news.title: RERA has ensured transparency in real estate sector in Bihar: Government
news.para: Addressing a workshop organised here to mark five years of implementation of Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act in the state, Singh said RERA-Bihar has dispelled the fears that creation of the authority would lead to licence raj in the sector.

news.title: Telangana government to inaugurate 310 2BHK houses in Bansilalpet
news.para: The project constructed at a cost of 23 crore consists of 310 double bedroom houses which is part of Greater Hyderabad Municipal Corporation (GHMC) target to provide 1 lakh houses across 111 locations.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC stays demolition drive at Chandigarh's Janta Colony
news.para: Davinder and 18 other colony residents claimed in the petition they were staying there for last many years and were eligible for houses under the slum rehabilitation scheme.

news.title: About 315 in Mann-Mhalunge to get property cards by May-end
news.para: Officials from the Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA) stated that 150 plot owners had been given the property cards.

news.title: Expedite LiDAR survey of properties: Navi Mumbai civic body
news.para: ​According to NMMC, around 70 percent on-site mobile van LiDAR survey of properties has been completed. The survey is being conducted in two stages such as on-site visit and aerial survey by drone with the use of LiDAR technology.

news.title: Delay may stall property tax relief for colony residents in Chandigarh
news.para: The last date to deposit property tax is May 31, after which heavy penalty and interest will be imposed on tax payers who failed to deposit the amount. Therefore, the authority needs to take a decision early.

news.title: Pay property tax by June 30 and get 10% rebate: Nagpur civic body
news.para: The civic body has also announced 10% and 5% rebate on property tax for those paying up before June 30 and December 31, respectively.

news.title: Dubai's Emaar Properties reports $610 million profit in Q1 2022
news.para: Emaar said it had a sales backlog of $12.3 billion at the end of the first quarter, which will be recognised in the future.

news.title: Flat owners in Maradu not entitled to any interest on amounts paid by them to builders: SC
news.para: ​A bench of Justices L Nageswara Rao and B R Gavai said in the present case, the flat-owners have purchased their apartments by paying installments somewhere between 2007 and 2013 depending on the construction of the particular building complex.

news.title: IIFL Home Finance aims Rs 7,200 crore home loans with ADB in Telangana, Andhra by 2025
news.para: The company said with a total disbursement of Rs 2,448 crore in these two states, it benefitted over 17,000 households as on March 31, 2022.

news.title: Citizens fume over delay in MahaRERA orders' execution
news.para: While the Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) bench issues the orders within its time-frame, citizens have complained of waiting from five months to even two years for the orders to get implemented.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government seeks housing scam report from GDA
news.para: ​The move comes days after the state government suspended former Ghaziabad district magistrate Nidhi Kesarwani in connection with alleged irregularities in acquiring land for the DME.
